title: Bushfires Rage As Victoria Faces Hottest Day Since Black Saturday Summer | 10 News
description: Victoria has sweltered through its hottest day since the deadly Black Saturday summer as six major fires burn across the state. Firefighters faced a particularly difficult day in Gellibrand in the Otways region where an out-of-control fire has more than doubled in size, with concerns about an approaching wind change. People are being asked to watch for signs of potentially deadly heat-related conditions as parts of the state face day four of the intense heatwave.
